forecastFinish.columnDescription: The planned finish date of a project's remaining Forecast cost.

estToCompleteCost.columnDescription: The estimated cost needed to complete the project.

ytdSpendCost.columnDescription: A measurement of capital spent on a project starting from the beginning of the year up to the present date. YTD Spends provide an overview of the total amount of spends accrued on a project over the current Period Year.

earnedValueCost.columnDescription: The value of work performed on a project in reference to the approved budget for the project. The cost value used for the Earned Value Management of a project. Earned Value Management allows project managers to quantify project progress and objectively measure a project's success.

cityName.columnDescription: The city name for a location.

proposedBudgetBase.columnDescription: The Proposed Budget for the project as allocated by the capital planner. Project managers can measure the proposed budget for their projects against their own planned budgets and project forecasts. If necessary, managers can request the planner make changes to the proposed budget allocated to their projects during capital plan scenario reviews. Becomes the projects Current Approved Budget once the capital plan scenario is approved.

locationName.columnDescription: A name for the location that your users will understand and recognize.

schedFinish.columnDescription: The calculated latest early finish date, which is based on the schedule most recently generated for the project.

linkForecastToSpends.columnDescription: Enables you to link project Forecast data to project Spends data. When linked any updates to the project's Spends values will automatically be applied to the project's Forecast values.

spendEffectiveDate.columnDescription: The month in which a spend value was last added to the project.

postalCode.columnDescription: The postal code, post code, or zip code of a location.

description.columnDescription: The detailed summary for the project. The description provides more information than short names or titles. It can give background information or establish a purpose for the item. These details help differentiate between items with similar names and are especially useful in multi-user environments.

forecastCost.columnDescription: The total estimation of a project's remaining costs. Once projects have begun, project managers update the project forecast to represent remaining cost estimates for the duration of the project's life cycle.

longitude.columnDescription: The geographical coordinate for the longitude of the location. The default format for longitude is decimal degrees format, but the format you need to use will depend on your geolocation service.

currentApprovedBudget.columnDescription: The total approved budget currently allocated to the project. Current Approved Budget values are derived from the Proposed Budget set by the capital planner. A Proposed Budget becomes a Current Approved Budget after the capital plan scenario has undergone the approval process.

costPerfIndex.columnDescription: The measure of a project's cost efficiency. A value less than 1 indicates the project's Actual Cost has exceeded its planned value.

mustFinishBy.columnDescription: The latest date on which the scheduled activities must be complete for a project.

status.columnDescription: The current status of a project. Proposal: The project is a project proposal and has not been extensively planned nor accrued any costs. Rejected: The project proposal has been rejected and will not be initiated as a project. Planned: The project is currently planned for execution. Project managers input expected project costs and other project data during this stage. Active: The project is currently active and being executed. Inactive: The project has been rendered inactive and will temporarily accrue no costs. Complete: The project has been successfully completed and will no longer accrue costs.

stateCode.columnDescription: A unique identifier for the state or province.

returnOnInvestment.columnDescription: The percentage resulting from division of the expected returns of an investment by the investment costs of a project or portfolio. For example, a project is expected to cost 1.0 million dollars with a total benefit of 1.2 million dollars. Its Net Present Value is $200,000. The Return on Investment is 20%.

code.columnDescription: The unique identifier for a project set by the user who created the project.

paybackPeriod.columnDescription: The estimate of the length of time that will transpire before net profits recover the initial and periodic costs of an investment to carry out the selected project.

actualCost.columnDescription: Total costs accrued on a project within a given time period. The Actual Cost data for the project's life cycle is pulled from the P6 EPPM schedule. Actual Cost data is only available when the application is connected with P6 EPPM and is not editable. In P6 EPPM, the Actual Cost value is calculated as Actual Labor Costs plus Actual Nonlabor Costs plus Actual Material Costs plus Actual Expense Costs.

addressLine2.columnDescription: The second line of the address of a location. This might be a neighborhood or town.

addressLine1.columnDescription: The first line of the address of a location. This might be the building number and street address.

url.columnDescription: The link to a website related to the project.

spendFinish.columnDescription: The finish date for the project spends.

planStart.columnDescription: The start date for the time phased Planned Budget of the project. Planned Budget cost spread will adjust when this date is changed. The Project Planned Start also represents the earliest date that activities can occur within a project schedule.

schedPerfIndex.columnDescription: The measure of the work accomplished as a percentage of the work scheduled on a project. Schedule Performance Index indicates whether you are meeting earned and planned values within your project schedule. A value less than 1 indicates that less work was performed than was scheduled.

actualDuration.columnDescription: The Actual Duration represents the total working time between the project Actual Start and Actual Finish for a project.

estAtCompleteCost.columnDescription: The expected total cost of the project when the defined scope of work will be completed.

owner.columnDescription: The manager or person responsible for the project.

lastModifiedBy.columnDescription: The user name of the user who last made changes to the item.

spendForecastVar.columnDescription: The total and time phased variance between the project's Spends and Forecast.

latitude.columnDescription: The geographical coordinate for the latitude of the location. The default format for latitude is decimal degrees format, but the format you need to use will depend on your geolocation service.

proposedPlanVar.columnDescription: The total and time phased variance between the project's Proposed Budget and Planned Budget.

projectIntegrationType.columnDescription: Specifies if the project is integrated with another application.

strgyPriorityNum.columnDescription: The project’s priority in the strategic plan. This priority value ranges from 1 to 10,000 with a default of 500. Use of the priority value, such as whether to place higher priority at the lower end of the scale, toward the endpoint 1, or at the higher end, toward 10,000, is at the discretion of the user. This field is not used for calculating data.

startDateVariance.columnDescription: The duration between the project's start date and default snapshot. When the field value is generated through a P6 EPPM connection, then it represents the duration between the start date in the current project and the baseline start date.

startDate.columnDescription: The date on which work on the project starts.

finishDateVariance.columnDescription: The duration between the project's finish date and default snapshot. When the field value is generated through a P6 EPPM connection, then it represents the duration between the finish date in the current project and the baseline finish date.

riskLevel.columnDescription: The risk level assigned to the project. Projects can have a risk level of very high, high, medium, low, or very low. You can use risk level to determine what projects should be included in your plans, as well as which projects should be of priority.

scheduleVariance.columnDescription: The measure of schedule performance on a project. A negative value indicates that less work was actually performed than was scheduled.

spendStart.columnDescription: The start date for the project spends.

remainingDuration.columnDescription: The duration between the Project Start and Project Finish.

actualFinish.columnDescription: The Actual Finish displays the date on which a project is considered complete.

reportCycleNamingBoundary.columnDescription: Determines when period names will be reset. The options available are based on the selection for Reporting Cycle. The standard calendar start and end dates are used as boundaries for resetting periods.

currency.columnDescription: The currency used by the project. The project currency can differ from the base currency.

plannedBudget.columnDescription: The planned total cost of a project as defined by the project manager. Planners can use Planned Budgets to determine how to allocate a plan's Proposed Budget values to projects, as well as what projects are reasonable to include in the current capital plan.

intRateOfReturn.columnDescription: The quantitative measurement used to compare the profitability of project investments. The rate at which investors will receive returns on their investments in a project.

parentId.columnDescription: The workspace the project is associated with.

forecastStart.columnDescription: The planned start date of a project's remaining Forecast cost.

spendPlannedBudgetVar.columnDescription: The total and time phased variance between the project's Spends and Planned Budget.

spendCost.columnDescription: The total actual spends incurred on a project throughout its lifecycle, such as the costs of invoices, payments, or accruals. Spends can be linked to the project Forecast to apply any new spend data to the project's forecast curve. Time phasing for each curve is linked, so a spend added in February 2014 will be applied to the Forecast in February 2014. Linking Spends and Forecast enables you to combine costs already incurred on a project with the project's predicted future costs effectively creating an at completion curve. Spends cannot be edited if a project has a status of Proposal.

addedBy.columnDescription: The user name of the user who added the item.

actualStart.columnDescription: The Actual Start indicates the date work on the project began.

percentComplete.columnDescription: The estimated percentage of work that has been completed on the project.

addedDate.columnDescription: The date on which the item was added.

netPresentValue.columnDescription: The difference between the present value (PV) of the future cash flows from current investments and project costs.

finishDate.columnDescription: The date on which all project work is complete.

costVariance.columnDescription: The measure of cost performance on a project. A negative value indicates that the Actual Cost has exceeded the planned value.

planFinish.columnDescription: The finish date for the time phased Planned Budget of the project. Planned Budget cost spread will adjust when this date is changed.

forecastCurrApprVar.columnDescription: The total and time phased variance between the project's Forecast and Current Approved Budget.

profitabilityIndex.columnDescription: The index based on the value of a project's present values divided by initial project investments.

pegRate.columnDescription: The custom exchange rate for a pegged exchange rate.

dataDate.columnDescription: The progress point, or "as-of date", for activities in the project. Project status is up-to-date as of the data date. You can set the data date when you schedule the project, or you can set it manually. The data date is also used for updating the dates of scope assignments and work packages when they are not linked to activities.

stateName.columnDescription: The state, region, or province of a location.

plannedValueCost.columnDescription: The amount of approved capital spent on a scheduled portion of work on a project. Planned Value Cost is often used for Earned Value Management.

lastModifiedDate.columnDescription: The most recent date on which changes were made to the item.

yearEndForecastCost.columnDescription: Total forecast at the end of year actuals till date, with respect to the current year.

plannedDuration.columnDescription: The duration between Project Planned Start and Project Planned Finish.

exchangeRateType.columnDescription: The type of exchange rate. Floating: A fixed, user-defined exchange rate. Pegged: Follows the exchange rates defined at the workspace.

measure.name: savings
measure.description: Savings acheived over a period of time

measure.name: Project on time
measure.description: Indicates the percent of projects that are on time
